## Key concepts

The following are the main ARM resource types exposed by this library:

| Resource class | Represents |
|---|---|
| `DataBoxEdgeDeviceResource` | A Data Box Edge physical device registered in Azure |
| `BandwidthScheduleResource` | A bandwidth throttling schedule for a device |
| `DataBoxEdgeJobResource` | An asynchronous job running on a device (e.g., firmware update) |
| `DataBoxEdgeOrderResource` | The order placed for a device |
| `DataBoxEdgeAlertResource` | An alert raised by a device |
| `DataBoxEdgeStorageAccountResource` | A storage account endpoint configured on the device |
| `DataBoxEdgeRoleResource` | A compute role (IoT, Kubernetes, etc.) running on the device |

Each resource type supports the standard Azure Resource Manager CRUD operations. Paginated list results are returned as `AsyncPageable` or `Pageable`.

## Examples

The following example shows how to list all Data Box Edge devices in a subscription and print their names.

```
ArmClient client = new ArmClient(new DefaultAzureCredential());
SubscriptionResource subscription = await client.GetDefaultSubscriptionAsync();

await foreach (DataBoxEdgeDeviceResource device in subscription.GetDataBoxEdgeDevicesAsync())
{
    Console.WriteLine(device.Data.Name);
}
```

The following example shows how to get a specific device and retrieve its current properties.

```
ArmClient client = new ArmClient(new DefaultAzureCredential());
ResourceGroupResource resourceGroup = client.GetResourceGroupResource(
    ResourceGroupResource.CreateResourceIdentifier(&#34;&#34;, &#34;&#34;));

DataBoxEdgeDeviceCollection devices = resourceGroup.GetDataBoxEdgeDevices();
DataBoxEdgeDeviceResource device = await devices.GetAsync(&#34;&#34;);

Console.WriteLine($&#34;Device: {device.Data.Name}, SKU: {device.Data.Sku?.Name}, Status: {device.Data.DataBoxEdgeDeviceStatus}&#34;);
```
```

